# VTOP – VIT On TOP System

## Problem Statement
Students, faculty, parents, and alumni often need quick and secure access to academic and institutional data. Currently, accessing this information can be time-consuming and manual. This project provides a centralized, role-based system to allow each type of user to access relevant information easily.

## Scope of the Project
- Role-based access for four types of users: Student, Employee, Parent, Alumni
- Display of attendance, marks, and weekly timetable for students
- Display of courses and student list for employees
- Display of child’s information and attendance for parents
- Display of passout details and events for alumni
- Secure login and logout 
- CLI-based interface, easily expandable for database or GUI integration in the future

## Target Users
- VIT Students
- Faculty / Employees
- Parents of students
- Alumni

## High-Level Features
- User authentication with role-based menu
- View attendance, marks, and timetable (Student)
- View assigned courses and students under supervision (Employee)
- View child details and overall attendance (Parent)
- View passout details and alumni events (Alumni)
- Logout 
